ntion%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGautam%20Bhatia%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbooks%2Fbooks-reviews%2Findia-government-judge-supreme-court-justice-people%2Farticle67247636.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20his%20recent%20book%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3E%20Unsealed%20Covers%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20written%20about%20how%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20pursued%20a%20practice%20of%20%E2%80%9Cjudicial%20evasion%E2%80%9D%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20while%20transitioning%20into%20an%20executive%E2%80%99s%20court%2C%20from%20being%20an%20anti-majoritarian%20court%20of%20late.%20The%20court%2C%20under%20the%20last%20few%20Chief%20Justices%2C%20failed%20to%20ask%20tough%20questions%20or%20challenge%20the%20Modi%20government%20while%20doing%20its%20bit%20in%20passing%20more%20%E2%80%98pro-government%E2%80%99%20judgments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20its%20recent%20order%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-law%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-verdict-9163729%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Estands%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20this%20attitude.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20the%20court%20will%20look%20into%20the%20discussed%20evidence%20of%20alleged%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements%20may%20well%20go%20on%20to%20define%20the%20future%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20democracy%20and%20transparency%20in%20political%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndependent%20media%20platforms%20have%20also%20done%20a%20phenomenal%20job%20in%20exposing%20the%20level%20of%20corruption%20facilitated%20by%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20(see%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnramind%2Fstatus%2F1768564316742287442%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20a%20thread).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20has%20the%20information%20it%20needs%20to%20assert%20its%20power%2C%20if%20it%20wants%20to%20scrap%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20and%20call%20(even%20if%20possible)%20for%20a%20delay%20to%20the%20upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20just%20a%20few%20weeks%20away.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20how%20most%20parties%20in%20this%20election%2C%20especially%20the%20BJP%20which%20has%20the%20largest%20share%20of%20funding%20from%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20have%20sourced%20their%20funds%2C%20there%20is%20a%20strong%20case%20for%20the%20apex%20court%20to%20exercise%20its%20discretion%20in%20upholding%20the%20constitutional%20integrity%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%20and%20not%20letting%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20happen%20unless%20a%20more%20transparent%20funding%20process%20is%20installed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20real%20question%20is%20whether%20the%20court%2C%20which%20raised%20critical%20questions%20on%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%2C%20will%20challenge%20SBI%20to%20release%20more%20data%20and%20then%20subsequently%20question%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20way%20it%20has%20engaged%20with%20its%20donors.%20Can%20this%20lead%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20being%20disqualified%20from%20contesting%20in%20the%20upcoming%20national%20elections%20even%20if%20the%20scheme%20isn%E2%80%99t%20scrapped%3F%20Or%2C%20is%20there%20a%20juridical%20case%20for%20setting%20a%20strong%20deterrence%2C%20in%20case%20of%20a%20political%20party%2C%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Elegalising%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecorruption%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20through%20a%20funding%20scheme%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20one%20waits%20for%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20next%20move%20and%20whether%20it%20will%20choose%20to%20act%20against%20those%20found%20guilty%2C%20what%E2%80%99s%20clear%20is%20how%20India%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20democracy%20at%20this%20moment%20remains%20challenged%20from%20an%20enlarged%20trust%20deficit%20and%20an%20illiberal%20turn%20like%20never%20seen%20before.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%2C%20Dean%2C%20IDEAS%2C%20Office%20of%20InterDisciplinary%20Studies%2C%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20He%20is%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20a%202024%20Fall%20Academic%20Visitor%20to%20Faculty%20of%20Asian%20and%20Middle%20Eastern%20Studies%2C%20University%20of%20Oxford.%20He%20has%20held%20Visiting%20Professorships%20with%20University%20of%20London%E2%80%99s%20Birkbeck%20College%20(UK)%2C%20University%20of%20Ottawa%20(Canada)%2C%20Carleton%20University%20(Canada)%2C%20Stellenbosch%20University%20(South%20Africa)%2C%20FGV%20(Rio%2C%20Brazil)%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710766826000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15105735%2FUntitled-design-8-3.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpoll-bonds-as-indias-electoral-democracy-remains-challenges-what-will-be-scs-next-move%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22How%20the%20court%20will%20look%20into%20the%20discussed%20evidence%20of%20alleged%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements%20may%20well%20go%20on%20to%20define%20the%20future%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20democracy%20and%20transparency%20in%20political%20funding.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpoll-bonds-as-indias-electoral-democracy-remains-challenges-what-will-be-scs-next-move%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20GDC%202024%3A%20How%20Annual%20Video%20Game%20Conference%20Has%20Pivoted%20Programming%20Amid%20Industrywide%20Layoffs%22%2C%22