ight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20a%20paradigm%20shift%2C%20originally%20expounded%20by%20Thomas%20Kuhn%2C%20is%20centred%20around%20the%20profound%20transformation%20in%20foundational%20assumptions%20within%20prevailing%20theories.%20Its%20applicability%20extends%20far%20beyond%20the%20realms%20of%20science%20to%20areas%20like%20policymaking.%20This%20theory%20posits%20that%20significant%20progress%20often%20occurs%20not%20through%20gradual%20improvement%20but%20through%20revolutionary%20changes%20that%20redefine%20fundamental%20understandings.%20In%20the%20domain%20of%20policymaking%2C%20this%20manifests%20as%20a%20departure%20from%20established%20norms%20and%20practices%20in%20response%20to%20accumulating%20anomalies%20or%20inefficiencies%20that%20the%20current%20paradigm%20cannot%20satisfactorily%20address.%20This%20paves%20the%20way%20for%20innovative%20frameworks%20that%20better%20tackle%20contemporary%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmbracing%20The%20Developed%20World%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDrawing%20a%20parallel%20to%20Kuhn's%20theory%2C%20India's%20evolving%20stance%20on%20trade%20policy%20and%20Regional%20Trade%20Agreements%20(RTAs)%20exemplifies%20a%20strategic%20paradigm%20shift%20within%20its%20economic%20policy%20framework.%20Historically%2C%20our%20RTAs%20were%20not%20with%20our%20major%20trading%20partners.%20Moving%20away%20from%20its%20traditional%20focus%20on%20just%20South-South%20cooperation%2C%20India%20has%20progressively%20embraced%20RTAs%20with%20the%20developed%20world.%20This%20pivot%20reflects%20a%20recognition%20of%20the%20mutual%20benefits%20that%20can%20be%20derived%20from%20enhanced%20market%20access%20for%20Indian%20goods%20and%20services%20in%20these%20economies%2C%20signalling%20a%20significant%20re-evaluation%20of%20India's%20trade%20strategies%20in%20favour%20of%20fostering%20economic%20growth%20and%20development%20through%20more%20integrated%20global%20trade%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELatest%20in%20this%20series%20of%20RTAs%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fkey-facts-about-indias-100-billion-deal-with-european-trade-group-5211586%5C%22%3ETrade%20and%20Economic%20Participation%20Agreement%20(TEPA)%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwatershed-moment-pm-modi-on-100-billion-trade-deal-with-european-trade-group-5213502%5C%22%3EEuropean%20Free%20Trade%20Association%20(EFTA)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwatershed-moment-pm-modi-on-100-billion-trade-deal-with-european-trade-group-5213502%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esigned%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20India%20on%20March%2010.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fwebstories%2Ffeature%2Fswiss-chocolates-watches-to-get-cheaper-for-indians-14503%5C%22%3EThrough%20TEPA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%20aims%20to%20enhance%20its%20trade%20and%20economic%20ties%2C%20thereby%20stimulating%20growth%2C%20employment%2C%20and%20technological%20advancements%20within%20its%20own%20economy.%20Such%20agreements%20underscore%20the%20importance%20of%20RTAs%20in%20bridging%20the%20economic%20divide%20between%20developing%20and%20developed%20nations%2C%20ultimately%20contributing%20to%20global%20economic%20prosperity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20TEPA%20Is%20Significant%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETEPA%20is%20characterised%20as%20a%20modern%20and%20ambitious%20pact%2C%20underpinned%20by%20unprecedented%20commitments%2C%20including%20a%20binding%20investment%20of%20%24100%20billion%20and%20the%20creation%20of%201%20million%20direct%20jobs%20in%20India%20over%20the%20next%2015%20years.%20The%20agreement%2C%20spanning%2014%20comprehensive%20chapters%2C%20focuses%20on%20enhancing%20market%20access%2C%20trade%20facilitation%2C%20investment%20promotion%2C%20and%20more.%20It%20ultimately%20aims%20to%20significantly%20boost%20the%20%E2%80%9CMake%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20initiative%20and%20provide%20ample%20opportunities%20for%20India's%20skilled%20workforce.%20EFTA's%20commitment%20to%20opening%20up%2092.2%25%20of%20its%20tariff%20lines%2C%20which%20encapsulates%2099.6%25%20of%20India's%20exports%2C%20alongside%20India's%20offer%20of%2082.7%25%20of%20its%20tariff%20lines%20covering%2095.3%25%20of%20EFTA's%20exports%2C%20underscores%20the%20depth%20of%20this%20economic%20collaboration.%20TEPA%20not%20only%20promises%20to%20strengthen%20India's%20export%20sectors%2C%20such%20as%20IT%20services%20and%20pharmaceuticals%2C%20but%20also%20paves%20the%20way%20for%20greater%20integration%20into%20European%20markets%2C%20particularly%20through%20Switzerland's%20significant%20trade%20connections%20with%20the%20EU.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20this%20is%20part%20of%20India's%20larger%20strategy%20to%20forge%20trade%20relationships%20with%20countries%20that%20have%20an%20appetite%20for%20Indian%20manufactured%20goods.%20India's%20strategic%20pivot%20toward%20RTAs%20marks%20a%20notable%20shift%20in%20its%20economic%20engagements%2C%20with%20implications%20for%20its%20aspirations%20of%20becoming%20a%20manufacturing%20alternative%20to%20China.%20A%202020%20analysis%20by%20the%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20(EAC-PM)%20of%20the%20'China%2B1'%20manufacturing%20strategy%20revealed%20a%20striking%20trend%3A%20industries%20that%20were%20diversifying%20away%20from%20China%20showed%20a%20pronounced%20preference%20for%20Vietnam.%20A%20critical%20factor%20behind%20this%20preference%20is%20Vietnam's%20extensive%20network%20of%20RTAs%20with%20developed%20economies%2C%20granting%20it%20preferential%20market%20access%20that%20companies%20find%20highly%20advantageous.%20This%20network%20of%20agreements%20positions%20Vietnam%20as%20a%20more%20competitive%20destination%20for%20firms%20looking%20to%20capitalise%20on%20these%20established%20trade%20links%2C%20which%20ultimately%20makes%20the%20country%20an%20attractive%20node%20in%20the%20global%20supply%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20And%20Vietnam%3A%20Two%20Different%20Outlooks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20strategic%20trade%20alliances%20of%20India%20and%20Vietnam%20in%202020%20showcase%20a%20tale%20of%20two%20contrasting%20approaches%20to%20economic%20partnerships.%20Vietnam's%20trade%20agreements%20are%20predominantly%20with%20nations%20that%20have%20advanced%20economies%2C%20reflecting%20its%20successful%20engagement%20with%20markets%20that%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20offer%20significant%20economic%20benefits%20and%20growth%20opportunities.%20This%20includes%20access%20to%20larger%20consumer%20bases%20and%20high-tech%20resources%2C%20positioning%20Vietnam%20favourably%20in%20the%20international%20trade%20arena.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20trade%20agreements%2C%20conversely%2C%20seem%20to%20be%20focused%20on%20forging%20stronger%20connections%20with%20other%20emerging%20economies.%20This%20preference%20may%20stem%20from%20various%20factors%2C%20including%20geopolitical%20strategy%2C%20the%20nature%20of%20India's%20exports%2C%20and%20the%20regulatory%20landscapes%20of%20potential%20developed-economy%20partners.%20While%20such%20alliances%20with%20developing%20nations%20can%20bolster%20regional%20solidarity%20and%20collective%20growth%2C%20they%20may%20also%20reflect%20the%20challenges%20India%20faces%20in%20penetrating%20the%20more%20established%20markets%2C%20which%20are%20often%20guarded%20by%20complex%20trade%20barriers%20and%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20India's%20web%20of%20RTAs%20largely%20included%20the%20developing%20world%2C%20fostering%20closer%20economic%20ties%20with%20countries%20across%20Africa%2C%20South%20America%2C%20and%20Asia.%20The%20data%20indicate%20that%20many%20of%20these%20RTAs%20were%20established%20between%202007%20and%202011%2C%20a%20period%20corresponding%20with%20the%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20(UPA)%20government%20in%20India.%20During%20this%20era%2C%20the%20RTAs%20appear%20to%20have%20resulted%20in%20a%20trade%20balance%20skewed%20in%20favour%20of%20India's%20partners.%20These%20countries%20managed%20to%20export%20more%20to%20India%2C%20benefiting%20from%20access%20to%20its%20vast%20market%2C%20while%20India's%20exports%20to%20them%20did%20not%20keep%20pace.%20The%20trade%20dynamics%20could%20be%20reflective%20of%20the%20terms%20negotiated%20within%20these%20RTAs%2C%20which%20may%20have%20been%20more%20favourable%20to%20the%20partner%20countries%2C%20or%20indicative%20of%20the%20competitive%20challenges%20Indian%20industries%20face%20in%20diversifying%20their%20export%20baskets%20or%20meeting%20the%20demand%20specifics%20of%20these%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Post-2020%20Shift%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%2C%20however%2C%20has%20taken%20cognisance%20of%20it%20and%20has%20brought%20a%20paradigm%20shift%20in%20its%20trade%20agreements.%20Post-2020%2C%20India%20has%20actively%20engaged%20in%20signing%20RTAs%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-will-not-rush-into-signing-free-trade-deals-says-union-minister-piyush-goyal-5112253%5C%22%3EFree%20Trade%20Agreements%20(FTAs)%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20developed%20countries%20and%20is%20currently%20in%20negotiations%20with%20others.%20A%20notable%20agreement%20is%20the%20India-Australia%20Economic%20Cooperation%20and%20Trade%20Agreement%20(ECTA)%20signed%20in%20April%202022%2C%20which%20marked%20the%20first%20trade%20agreement%20with%20a%20developed%20country%20after%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20The%20pact%20aims%20to%20enhance%20cooperation%20across%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20economic%20and%20commercial%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20nations%2C%20covering%20sectors%20like%20Trade%20in%20Goods%2C%20Trade%20in%20Services%2C%20Technical%20Barriers%20to%20Trade%20(TBT)%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20Australia%2C%20India%20has%20also%20revitalised%20its%20trade%20relations%20with%20the%20UAE%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fuae-indias-joint-statement-after-pm-modis-visit-4211370%5C%22%3EComprehensive%20Economic%20Partnership%20Agreement%20(CEPA)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20resumed%20in%20February%202022.%20The%20agreement%20aims%20to%20increase%20goods%20trade%20to%20%24100%20billion%20within%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%20with%20a%20potential%20to%20touch%20%24250%20billion%20by%202030.%20It%20is%20also%20expected%20to%20generate%20significant%20employment%20opportunities%20across%20various%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20also%20in%20the%20process%20of%20negotiating%20RTAs%20with%20the%20European%20Union%20and%20the%20UK%20as%20well%20as%20exploring%20Free%20Trade%20Agreements%20with%20Israel%20and%20the%20Gulf%20Cooperation%20Council%20(GCC)%20countries.%20These%20negotiations%20and%20agreements%20are%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20strategy%20to%20engage%20more%20closely%20with%20both%20developed%20and%20developing%20economies%20across%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Developing%20Nations%20Benefit%20From%20Partnerships%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20that%20between%20developed%20and%20developing%20nations%2C%20RTAs%20are%20more%20advantageous%20for%20the%20latter%20is%20an%20intriguing%20concept%20in%20international%20economics%2C%20supported%20by%20substantial%20empirical%20evidence.%20The%20benefits%20for%20developing%20countries%20often%20manifest%20through%20increased%20Foreign%20Direct%20Investment%20(FDI)%2C%20economic%20growth%2C%20and%20reduced%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDrawing%20parallels%20from%20the%20well-established%20concepts%20of%20%26quot%3Btrade%20creation%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btrade%20diversion%26quot%3B%20in%20international%20trade%20theory%2C%20RTAs%20can%20similarly%20influence%20investment%20patterns.%20%26quot%3BInvestment%20creation%26quot%3B%20refers%20to%20the%20phenomenon%20where%20new%20investment%20flows%20are%20generated%20due%20to%20the%20enhanced%20attractiveness%20of%20a%20market%20as%20part%20of%20a%20trade%20agreement.%20This%20could%20be%20due%20to%20reduced%20barriers%2C%20better%20market%20access%2C%20or%20a%20more%20stable%20and%20predictable%20investment%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Investment%20Boon%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20%26quot%3Binvestment%20diversion%26quot%3B%20occurs%20when%20investment%20is%20rerouted%20from%20more%20efficient%20non-member%20countries%20to%20less%20efficient%20member%20countries%20within%20an%20RTA%2C%20solely%20due%20to%20the%20preferential%20treatment%20afforded%20by%20the%20agreement.%20While%20investment%20diversion%20might%20seem%20detrimental%20at%20a%20global%20efficiency%20level%2C%20for%20developing%20countries%20within%20an%20RTA%2C%20this%20can%20still%20represent%20a%20significant%20boon%20as%20it%20brings%20in%20capital%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20expertise%20that%20might%20not%20have%20been%20accessible%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20studies%20have%20provided%20empirical%20backing%20for%20these%20concepts.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20research%20by%20Yeyati%20and%20colleagues%20demonstrates%20that%20FTAs%20between%20a%20home%20country%20and%20a%20host%20country%20are%20positively%20correlated%20with%20increased%20bilateral%20outward%20FDI.%20This%20suggests%20that%20when%20countries%20enter%20into%20trade%20agreements%2C%20businesses%20within%20these%20countries%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20invest%20in%20each%20other%2C%20driven%20by%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20FTA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EB%C3%BCthe%20and%20Milner's%20analysis%20further%20corroborates%20the%20positive%20impact%20of%20trade%20agreements%20on%20FDI%20inflows%2C%20specifically%20highlighting%20that%20developing%20countries%20that%20are%20part%20of%20numerous%20trade%20agreements%20tend%20to%20receive%20more%20FDI.%20This%20influx%20of%20investment%20is%20crucial%20for%20developing%20countries%20as%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20job%20creation%2C%20technology%20transfer%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20development%2C%20thereby%20fuelling%20economic%20growth%20and%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuality%20Of%20FTAs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20it's%20not%20just%20the%20existence%20of%20RTAs%20that%20matters%2C%20but%20also%20their%20quality.%20Agreements%20that%20include%20comprehensive%20liberal%20investment%20rules%20and%20equitable%20dispute%20settlement%20mechanisms%20are%20particularly%20effective%20in%20attracting%20FDI.%20These%20features%20reduce%20the%20risks%20and%20uncertainties%20associated%20with%20investing%20in%20foreign%20markets%2C%20making%20developing%20countries%20more%20attractive%20destinations%20for%20foreign%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20these%20agreements%20and%20ongoing%20negotiations%20signify%20a%20shift%20in%20India's%20trade%20policy%20towards%20more%20strategic%20and%20beneficial%20trade%20partnerships%2C%20focusing%20on%20reducing%20trade%20deficits%20and%20enhancing%20economic%20cooperation.%20The%20impact%20of%20these%20agreements%20could%20be%20multifaceted%2C%20potentially%20leading%20to%20increased%20trade%20flows%2C%20enhanced%20foreign%20investment%2C%20job%20creation%2C%20and%20a%20stronger%20position%20for%20India%20in%20the%20global%20trade%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bibek%20Debroy%20is%20Chairman%20%26amp%3B%20Aditya%20Sinha%20is%20OSD%2C%20Research%20at%20the%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710764460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F20