tch%3Fv%3DwOZUuPhgMjc%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CNo%20corrupt%20person%20will%20be%20left%2C%20I%20am%20making%20this%20promise%20to%20the%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHome%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Famit-shah-first-reaction-electoral-bonds-row-we-introduced-it-to-wipe-out-black-money-2515470-2024-03-15%5C%22%3Edefending%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20beginning%20towards%20a%20solution%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20at%20the%20India%20Today%20Conclave%20on%20March%2015%2C%202024%20that%20he%20was%20willing%20to%20debate%20with%20any%20person%20on%20any%20forum%20that%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20brought%20to%20end%20black%20money%20in%20Indian%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMocking%20at%20any%20link%20between%20the%20functioning%20of%20central%20investigating%20agencies%2C%20including%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20raids%2C%20to%20the%20electoral%20funding%20of%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fi-fear-black-money-will-be-back-says-shah-sitharaman-says-ed-link-just-assumption-9216938%2F%5C%22%3Ebragged%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CFor%20all%20you%20know%20the%20money%20was%20given%20earlier%20and%20in%20spite%20of%20that%20we%20went%20knocking%20at%20their%20doors.%20Am%20I%20making%20sense%3F%20No%3F%20What%20if%20the%20companies%20gave%20money%20and%20after%20that%20we%20still%20went%20knocking%20on%20their%20doors%20through%20ED%3F%20Is%20that%20a%20probability%20or%20not%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CStill%20went%20knocking%E2%80%9D%20shockingly%20suggests%20knowledge%20that%20the%20raided%20companies%20were%20donating%20to%20the%20party!%20There%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20even%20a%20whisper%20that%20there%20could%20be%20quid%20pro%20quo%20despite%20what%20was%20said%20in%20the%20February%2014%2C%202024%20judgment%20of%20the%20apex%20court%20and%20despite%20the%20initial%20revelations%20about%20donors%20and%20donees%20in%20the%20data%20released%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHiding%20behind%20the%20fig%20leaf%20of%20opacity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20was%20not%20answered%20by%20the%20Union%20home%20minister%20and%20finance%20minister%20was%20why%20was%20the%20ruling%20party%20accepting%20thousands%20of%20crores%20of%20rupees%20from%20companies%20that%20were%20being%20investigated%2C%20raided%20and%2For%20prosecuted%20by%20agencies%20of%20the%20Centre.%20The%20short%20answer%20would%20be%20that%20they%20did%20not%20know%20who%20the%20donors%20were%2C%20otherwise%20they%20would%20be%20open%20to%20prosecution%20for%20extortion%2C%20an%20accusation%20that%20has%20been%20made%20by%20opposition%20leaders%20like%20Rahul%20Gandhi.%20The%20minimal%20charge%20of%20political%20and%20financial%20immorality%20of%20accepting%20donation%20from%20companies%20being%20investigated%2C%20prosecuted%20and%2For%20raided%20by%20Central%20agencies%20is%20being%20defended%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20anonymity%20and%20opacity%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApex%20court%E2%80%99s%20removal%20of%20the%20fig%20leaf%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20fig%20leaf%20of%20lack%20of%20knowledge%2C%20about%20donors%2C%20by%20the%20ruling%20party%20was%20systematically%20removed%20by%20the%20Constitutional%20Bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20by%20its%20judgement%20to%20expose%20possible%20corruption%20in%20governance%20anchored%20in%20quid%20pro%20quo%20between%20the%20corporate%20donors%20and%20the%20political%20donee.%20While%20holding%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Scheme%20violative%20of%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20court%20systematically%20(paragraph%20103)%20rubbished%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20it%20did%20not%20know%20who%20the%20donors%20were.%20The%20court%20observed%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20submission%20of%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20is%20that%20the%20political%20party%20which%20receives%20the%20contribution%20does%20not%20know%20of%20identity%20of%20the%20contributor%20because%20neither%20the%20bond%20would%20have%20their%20name%20nor%20could%20the%20bank%20discloses%20such%20details%20to%20the%20political%20party.%20We%20do%20not%20agree%20with%20this%20submission.%20While%20it%20is%20true%20that%20the%20law%20prescribes%20anonymity%20as%20a%20central%20characteristic%20of%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Ede%20jure%20%3C%2Fem%3Eanonymity%20of%20the%20contributors%20does%20not%20translate%20to%20%3Cem%3Ede%20facto%20%3C%2Fem%3Eanonymity.%20The%20Scheme%20is%20not%20fool-proof.%20There%20are%20sufficient%20gaps%20in%20the%20Scheme%20which%20enable%20political%20parties%20to%20know%20the%20particulars%20of%20the%20contributions%20made%20to%20them.%20Clause%2012%20of%20the%20Scheme%20states%20that%20the%20bond%20can%20be%20encashed%20only%20by%20the%20political%20party%20by%20depositing%20it%20in%20the%20designated%20bank%20account.%20The%20contributor%20could%20physically%20hand%20over%20the%20electoral%20bond%20to%20an%20office%20bearer%20of%20the%20political%20party%20or%20to%20the%20legislator%20belonging%20to%20the%20political%20party%2C%20or%20it%20could%20have%20been%20sent%20to%20the%20office%20of%20the%20political%20party%20with%20the%20name%20of%20the%20contributor%2C%20or%20the%20contributor%20could%20after%20depositing%20the%20electoral%20bond%20disclose%20the%20particulars%20of%20the%20contribution%20to%20a%20member%20of%20the%20political%20party%20for%20them%20to%20cross-verify.%20Further%2C%20according%20to%20the%20data%20on%20contributions%20made%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20ninety%20four%20percent%20of%20the%20contributions%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20have%20been%20made%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20one%20crore.%20Electoral%20bonds%20provide%20economically%20resourced%20contributors%20who%20already%20have%20a%20seat%20at%20the%20table%20selective%20anonymity%20vis-a%CC%80-vis%20the%20public%20and%20not%20the%20political%20party.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20has%20the%20government%20shied%20away%20from%20investigating%20quid%20pro%20quo%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20paragraph%20172%20of%20the%20apex%20court%20judgment%2C%20the%20bench%20observed%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20deletion%20of%20the%20mandate%20of%20disclosing%20the%20particulars%20of%20contributions%20violates%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20the%20voter%20since%20they%20would%20not%20possess%20information%20about%20the%20political%20party%20to%20which%20the%20contribution%20was%20made%20which%2C%20as%20we%20have%20held%20above%2C%20is%20necessary%20to%20identify%20corruption%20and%20quid%20pro%20quo%20transactions%20in%20governance.%E2%80%9D%20In%20paragraph%20201%20the%20court%20bluntly%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20reason%20for%20political%20contributions%20by%20companies%20is%20as%20open%20as%20day%20light.%20Even%20the%20learned%20Solicitor%20General%20did%20not%20deny%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20hearings%20that%20corporate%20donations%20are%20made%20to%20receive%20favours%20through%20%3Cem%3Equid%20pro%20quo%20%3C%2Fem%3Earrangements.%E2%80%9D%20The%20court%C2%A0%20made%20it%20crystal%20clear%20in%20paragraph%20212%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccontributions%20made%20by%20companies%20are%20purely%20business%20transactions%20made%20with%20the%20intent%20of%20securing%20benefits%20in%20return%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20recalled%20that%20a%20~100%20crore%20Delhi%20liquor%20scam%20has%20led%20to%20the%20arrest%20of%20two%20ministers%20of%20AAP%20and%20to%20the%20arrest%20of%20MLC%20K.%20Kavitha%20on%20March%2016%2C%202024.%20This%2C%20even%20when%20no%20money%20has%20been%20found.%20In%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scam%2C%20thousands%20of%20crores%20have%20been%20received%2C%20by%20ruling%20parties%20in%20Centre%20and%20states%2C%20from%20just%2014%20among%20the%20top%20donor%20companies%20that%20were%20being%20investigated%2C%20raided%20and%20prosecuted%20by%20the%20ED%2C%20CBI%20and%20or%20Income%20Tax%20Department.%20Yet%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20not%20even%20announced%20an%20inquiry%20into%20the%20quid%20pro%20quo%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20donors%20even%20though%20the%20initial%20data%2C%20however%20imperfect%2C%20is%20out%20in%20the%20public%20domain!%20This%20means%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20and%2For%20its%20agencies%20do%20not%20really%20agree%20with%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20apex%20court%20that%20there%20is%20or%20could%20be%20quid%20pro%20quo%20and%20corruption.%20Or%20worse%2C%20how%20can%20the%20ruling%20party%20in%20the%20Centre%20be%20expected%20to%20investigate%20itself%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApplying%20the%20AAP%20principle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20as%20if%20political%20parties%20cannot%20be%20investigated%20and%20prosecuted%20for%20corruption%20and%20or%20money%20laundering.%20Speaking%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20before%20a%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20(part%20of%20the%20present%20Constitutional%20Bench%20hearing%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case%20and%20in%20line%20to%20be%20next%20CJI)%20and%20S.V.N.%20Bhatti%20on%20behalf%20of%20CBI%20and%20ED%20in%20the%20alleged%20liquor%20scam%20involving%20~100%20crore%20kickbacks%2C%20ASG%20S.V.%20Raju%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdelhi%2Faap-may-be-made-accused-in-excise-probe-ed-cbi-to-sc%2Farticleshow%2F104480362.cms%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20received%20instructions%20to%20make%20a%20statement.%20We%20are%20contemplating%20making%20AAP%20an%20accused%20and%20invoking%20Section%2070%20of%20PMLA%20with%20respect%20to%20vicarious%20liability.%E2%80%9D%20He%20was%20responding%20to%20a%20query%20from%20the%20bench%20as%20to%20why%20they%20had%20not%20made%20AAP%20an%20accused%20despite%20consistently%20alleging%20that%20it%20was%20the%20party%20that%20was%20the%20main%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20alleged%20scam.%20So%20therefore%20not%20only%20the%20apex%20court%2C%20but%20also%20the%20CBI%20and%20ED%20agree%20that%20political%20parties%20can%20possibly%20be%20investigated%20and%20prosecuted%20for%20corruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECourt-monitored%20investigation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20court-monitored%20investigation%20is%20necessary%20because%20the%20court%20has%20imputed%20knowledge%20to%20the%20government%2Fruling%20political%20party%20about%20the%20donors%20and%20their%20donations%2C%20despite%20the%20de%20jure%20anonymity%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%20It%20is%20not%20possible%20for%20the%20government%20to%20distance%20itself%20from%20the%20party!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20could%20constitute%20an%20SIT%2C%20principally%20consisting%20of%20retired%20ED%2C%20CBI%20and%20Income%20Tax%20officers%2C%20which%20could%20examine%2C%20investigate%20to%20the%20extent%20possible%2C%20and%20report%20on%20the%20quid%20pro%20quo%20mainly%20between%20the%20political%20party%20and%20the%20government%20in%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20donors%20that%20were%20under%20investigation%20or%20were%20raided%20and%2For%20were%20being%20prosecuted%20by%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20instrumentalities%2C%20mainly%20the%20ED%2C%20CBI%20and%20Income%20Tax.%20Other%20quid%20pro%20quos%20between%20state%20governments%20and%20parties%20and%20the%20donors%20would%20also%20have%20to%20be%20investigated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amount%20paid%20by%20the%20donors%20who%20were%20already%20being%20investigated%20and%2For%20raided%2F%20prosecuted%20by%20the%20agencies%20of%20the%20Centre%20should%20be%20impounded%20from%20the%20political%20parties%20(if%20unspent)%20and%20deposited%20in%20the%20Consolidated%20Fund%20of%20India%20as%20central%20revenues.%20Similarly%20donations%20received%20by%20parties%20in%20States%20where%20quid%20pro%20quo%20is%20revealed%20with%20specific%20donors%20would%20be%20required%20to%20be%20impounded%20and%20transferred%20to%20CFI.%20Third%2C%20all%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%20ought%20be%20made%20in%20a%20transparent%20manner%2C%20till%20parliament%20comes%20up%20with%20a%20law%20for%20transparent%20funding%20of%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Frahul-singh%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ERahul%20Singh%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20former%20civil%20servant%20who%20retired%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%2C%20Government%20of%20India.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710761432000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F18163351%2FIMG_3071.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwhy-a-court-monitored-probe-on-quid-pro-quo-involving-electoral-bonds-is-needed%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20minimal%20charge%20of%20political%20and%20financial%20immorality%20of%20accepting%20donation%20from%20companies%20being%20investigated%2C%20prosecuted%20and%2For%20raided%20by%20Central%20agencies%20is%20being%20defended%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20anonymity%20and%20opacity%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwhy-a-court-monitored-probe-on-quid-pro-quo-involving-electoral-bonds-is-needed%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%3A%20'Chaar%20June%20ko%20Chaar%20Sau%20Paar'%2C%20says%20PM%20Modi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710761359000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-03%2F18%2Ffull%2F1710759580-7702.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Felections%2Flok-sabha-election%2F2024-lok-sabha-elections-chaar-june