best-irish-pub-in-every-state-yelp%5C%22%3ESt.%20Patrick's%20Day%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20visited%20McSorley's%20Old%20Ale%20House%2C%20which%20was%20established%20in%201854.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20inexpensive%20prices%20and%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20food.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20was%20also%20surprised%20by%20how%20it%20made%20me%20feel%20pride%20as%20an%20Irish%20American.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20lived%20in%20New%20York%20City%20for%20almost%20four%20years%2C%20but%20I%20have%20never%20been%20to%20McSorley's%2C%20the%20oldest%20Irish%20pub%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcsorleys-bar-history-beer-photos-2017-11%5C%22%3EMcSorley's%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20most%20historic%20Irish%20tavern%20in%20New%20York%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20often%20called%20the%20oldest%20Irish%20tavern%20in%20America%20that's%20still%20in%20operation.%20Established%20in%201854%2C%20McSorley's%20is%20celebrating%20its%20170th%20anniversary%20this%20year%2C%20and%20it%20is%20certainly%20the%20place%20to%20go%20around%20St.%20Patrick's%20Day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20famous%2C%20McSorley's%20hasn't%20always%20been%20on%20the%20right%20side%20of%20history.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1970%2F08%2F11%2Farchives%2Fmcsorleys-admits-women-under-a-new-city-law-mcsorleys-is-forced-to.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20women%20have%20only%20been%20allowed%20inside%20the%20bar%20since%201970%2C%20when%20two%20members%20of%20the%20National%20Organization%20for%20Women%20sued%20the%20bar%20for%20violating%20the%20equal-protection%20ordinance%20of%20the%2014th%20Amendment.%20There%20were%20also%20no%20female%20bartenders%20until%20the%20mid-'90s%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbedfordandbowery.com%2F2020%2F12%2Fmcsorleys-first-female-bartender-keeps-its-spirit-alive%2Famp%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBedford%20%2B%20Bowery%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20St.%20Patrick's%20Day%202023%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20visit%20the%20bar%20given%20its%20rich%20history%20and%20connection%20to%20my%20heritage.%20My%20grandparents%20were%20first-generation%20Irish%20immigrants%20who%20later%20moved%20to%20England.%20That%20fact%2C%20in%20combination%20with%20my%20very%20Irish%20name%2C%20makes%20me%20proud%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraditional-irish-breakfast-recipe-review-st-patricks-day-2022-3%5C%22%3Eclose%20connection%20to%20my%20heritage.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20surprised%20by%20how%20much%20I%20enjoyed%20my%20experience%20at%20McSorley's%20during%20my%20visit%20last%20year.%20Here%20are%20some%20things%20that%20might%20surprise%20you%20about%20the%20oldest%20Irish%20bar%20in%20the%20country%20if%20you%20choose%20to%20visit%20yourself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20was%20surprised%20by%20McSorley's%20location%20in%20a%20very%20modern%20section%20of%20the%20East%20Village.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mcsorleys%20old%20ale%20house%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64145ae05f4f5400191a0c9e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20outside%20of%20McSorley's.%3Cp%3EErin%20McDowell%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20expected%20to%20find%20McSorley's%20on%20a%20quaint%20cobblestone%20street%20given%20its%20history%2C%20it's%20located%20in%20a%20built-up%20section%20of%20the%20East%20Village%20on%20East%207th%20Street%2C%20by%20Astor%20Place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20actually%20lived%20around%20the%20corner%20for%20a%20semester%20in%20college%2C%20and%2C%20in%20my%20opinion%2C%20this%20part%20of%20the%20East%20Village%20has%20very%20little%20old-world%20charm%20thanks%20to%20its%20high-rise%20buildings%2C%20businesses%2C%20and%20chain%20restaurants%2C%20despite%20being%20just%20a%20stone's%20throw%20away%20from%20one%20of%20the%20most%20historic%20establishments%20in%20the%20city.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20the%20ale%20house%20was%20founded%20by%20Irish%20immigrant%20John%20McSorley%20in%20the%201850s%2C%20this%20was%20a%20prime%20location%2C%20close%20to%20a%20transportation%20hub%20for%20horse%20carriages%20and%20a%20busy%20market%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcsorleys-bar-history-beer-photos-2017-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMcSorley's%20is%20cash-only%2C%20which%20I%20learned%20when%20I%20arrived.%20However%2C%20you'll%20find%20an%20ATM%20right%20out%20front.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mcsorleys%20old%20ale%20house%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64145b140308e00018553195%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20ATM%20outside%20McSorley's.%3Cp%3EErin%20McDowell%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20pretty%20standard%20at%20any%20cash-only%20bar%20or%20restaurant%20in%20New%20York%20City%20to%20find%20an%20ATM%20either%20inside%20or%20just%20outside%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20pleased%20that%20they%20had%20an%20ATM%20available%20so%20close%20by%2C%20but%20I%20couldn't%20spy%20any%20signs%20inside%20that%20made%20it%20immediately%20apparent%20it%20was%20cash-only%20%E2%80%94%20I%20didn't%20suss%20it%20out%20until%20I%20saw%20everyone%20else%20paying%20in%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20expected%20to%20find%20a%20lot%20of%20Irish%20pub%20food%2C%20and%20I%20did%2C%20but%20McSorley's%20also%20had%20distinctly%20American%20foods%20like%20hot%20dogs%20and%20hamburgers.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223379%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mcsorleys%20old%20ale%20house%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F641460175f4f5400191a0d56%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222534%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20menu%20at%20McSorley's.%3Cp%3EErin%20McDowell%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20menu%20at%20McSorley's%20is%20limited%2C%20but%20they%20had%20quite%20a%20few%20fan-favorite%20menu%20items%2C%20from%20burgers%20and%20a%20fried-chicken%20sandwich%20to%20more%20traditional%20items%20like%20corned-beef%20hash%20and%20chili.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20also%20surprised%20by%20how%20low%20the%20prices%20were%20at%20McSorley's%20compared%20to%20what%20I%20usually%20pay%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20I%20ordered%20a%20hamburger%20and%20fries%20for%20%2410%2C%20and%20two%20beers%20for%20%248.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20was%20overall%20pleasantly%20surprised%20by%20the%20burger%20at%20McSorley's%2C%20but%20I%20wish%20the%20cheese%20had%20been%20more%20melted.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mcsorleys%20old%20ale%20house%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64145b085f4f5400191a0cb5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20cheeseburger%20at%20McSorley's.%3Cp%3EErin%20McDowell%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20visited%20McSorley's%2C%20the%20bar%20was%20teeming%20with%20people%20and%20there%20were%20very%20few%20places%20to%20sit.%20I'm%20always%20a%20little%20hesitant%20about%20ordering%20bar%20food%20%E2%80%93%20you%20just%20never%20know%20what%20you're%20going%20to%20get%2C%20especially%20from%20places%20popular%20with%20tourists%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20was%20surprised%20by%20how%20much%20I%20liked%20the%20burger.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20beef%20patty%20was%20juicy%20and%20decently%20large%2C%20while%20the%20onions%20and%20tomatoes%20tasted%20very%20fresh.%20The%20fries%20were%20also%20piping%20hot%20when%20I%20received%20them%20and%20deliciously%20crispy.%20The%20only%20downside%20in%20my%20opinion%20was%20that%20the%20cheese%20on%20the%20cheeseburger%20wasn't%20melted%20on%20the%20patty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20for%20%2410%2C%20I%20was%20pleased%20with%20my%20dinner.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMcSorley's%20has%20only%20two%20options%20for%20alcoholic%20drinks%20%E2%80%94%20light%20or%20dark%20beer%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20serve%20two%20at%20a%20time%20per%20person%2C%20which%20definitely%20surprised%20me.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mcsorleys%20old%20ale%20house%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64145b1f5f4f5400191a0cc5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20beer%20at%20McSorley's.%3Cp%3EErin%20McDowell%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20paid%20%248%20for%20two%20beers%2C%20a%20light%20and%20a%20dark%20ale%2C%20which%20I%20was%20surprised%20by.%20I'm%20not%20a%20huge%20beer%20drinker%2C%20but%20even%20that%20seemed%20pretty%20inexpensive%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20beer%20prices%20have%20crept%20up%20over%20the%20years%2C%20of%20course.%20When%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcsorleys-bar-history-beer-photos-2017-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20Sarah%20Jacobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20visited%20in%202017%2C%20the%20beer%20cost%20%245.50.%20She%20noted%20that%20the%20beer%20cost%20only%20a%20dime%20per%20mug%20in%201940%2C%20and%20in%201966%2C%20two%20of%20the%20half-pints%20cost%2035%20cents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20guests%20also%20appeared%20to%20be%20surprised%20by%20their%20orders.%20When%20one%20guest%20ordered%20a%20light%20and%20a%20dark%20beer%20for%20himself%20and%20someone%20else%2C%20they%20seemed%20surprised%20when%20they%20were%20each%20handed%20two%20beers.%20The%20bartender%20then%20explained%20that%20they%20always%20give%20people%20two%20beers%20each.%20The%20beers%20are%20much%20smaller%20than%20your%20average%20pint.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fny.eater.com%2F2022%2F11%2F17%2F23462867%2Fmcsorleys-irish-saloon-cheap-beer-prices-nyc-restaurants%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEater%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20each%20mug%20holds%20roughly%206%20ounces%20per%20glass%20%E2%80%94%20a%20US%20pint%20holds%2016%20ounces%20%E2%80%94%20which%20makes%20each%20drink%20easier%20to%20finish%20and%20carry%20around%20the%20bar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20enjoyed%20both%20the%20light%20and%20the%20dark%20ale%2C%20though%20I%20preferred%20the%20light%2C%20and%20thought%20they%20went%20down%20smoothly.%20I%20could%20see%20why%20someone%20would%20want%20two%20at%20a%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20charm%20of%20McSorley's%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20low%20prices%2C%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20choice.%20In%20a%20city%20like%20New%20York%2C%20I'm%20accustomed%20to%20lengthy%20drink%20menus%20with%20steep%20prices.%20I%20actually%20enjoyed%20the%20lack%20of%20choice%2C%20which%20made%20ordering%20fast%20and%20simple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20was%20also%20surprised%20by%20just%20how%20much%20history%20was%20crammed%20onto%20every%20inch%20of%20the%20walls.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mcsorleys%20old%20ale%20house%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64145b350308e0001855319c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPictures%20hanging%20on%20the%20walls%20inside%20McSorley's.%3Cp%3EErin%20McDowell%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20every%20inch%20of%20the%20walls%20was%20adorned%20with%20old%20photos%2C%20newspaper%20clippings%2C%20pictures%20of%20Irish%20American%20presidents%2C%20and%20festive%20St.%20Patrick's%20Day%20decorations.%20A%20large%20flag%20hung%20behind%20the%20bar%20with%20the%20number%20169%20on%20it%20%E2%80%94