2%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20James%20Webb%20space%20telescope.%3Cp%3Edima_zel%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EScientists%20say%20they%20observed%20a%20planet%20that%20may%20have%20an%20ocean-covered%20surface%2C%20the%20Guardian%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20observations%20were%20made%20using%20NASA's%20James%20Webb%20space%20telescope.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20a%20Canadian%20research%20group%20said%20the%20planet%20is%20likely%20too%20hot%20for%20liquid%20water.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20say%20they%20have%20observed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fexoplanets.nasa.gov%2Fexoplanet-catalog%2F7571%2Ftoi-270-d%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeptune-like%3C%2Fa%3E%20planet%20that%20could%20be%20covered%20by%20a%20deep-water%20ocean%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fscience%2F2024%2Fmar%2F08%2Fastronomers-detect-waterworld-with-a-boiling-ocean-in-deep-space%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR05Ygwpv64-frgfibQcglp6qAZy2Gy55rZ-gvltUB3SeATacVWvt9zGXoA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20team%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20in%20the%20UK%20said%20it%20had%20found%20evidence%20of%20water%20vapor%20and%20chemical%20signatures%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20and%20methane%20on%20an%20exoplanet%20known%20as%20TOI-270%20d%2C%20which%20is%20around%2070%20light%20years%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20used%20NASA's%20James%20Webb%20space%20telescope%20to%20make%20observations%20of%20the%20planet%2C%20which%20has%20twice%20the%20radius%20of%20Earth%20and%20a%20mass%20of%204.78%20Earths%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fexoplanets.nasa.gov%2Fexoplanet-catalog%2F7571%2Ftoi-270-d%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENikku%20Madhusudhan%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20astrophysics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20who%20led%20the%20research%2C%20told%20the%20Guardian%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ocean%20could%20be%20upwards%20of%20100%20degrees%20%5BCelsius%5D%20or%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20with%20high%20atmospheric%20pressure%2C%20that%20ocean%20could%20still%20be%20liquid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20clear%20if%20it%20would%20be%20habitable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20planet%20is%20also%20tidally%20locked%2C%20meaning%20one%20side%20is%20left%20in%20constant%20darkness%20while%20the%20other%20faces%20its%20star%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ocean%20would%20be%20extremely%20hot%20on%20the%20day%20side.%20The%20night%20side%20could%20potentially%20host%20habitable%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20Madhusudhan%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20liquid%20ocean%20is%20the%20preferred%20premise%20set%20out%20in%20a%20paper%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aanda.org%2Farticles%2Faa%2Ffull_html%2F2024%2F03%2Faa48238-23%2Faa48238-23.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAstronomy%20%26amp%3B%20Astrophysics%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20also%20notes%20the%20lack%20of%20ammonia%20on%20TOI-270%20d%2C%20which%20it%20said%20was%20%26quot%3Bconsistent%20with%20predictions%20for%20a%20Hycean%20world%20with%20a%20planet-wide%20ocean%26quot%3B%20under%20a%20hydrogen-rich%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20group%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2403.03325%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECanadian%20researchers%20who%20also%20observed%20TOI-270%20d%20have%20disputed%20the%20Cambridge%20team's%20claims.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20they%20detected%20the%20same%20chemicals%20in%20the%20planet's%20atmosphere%2C%20one%20of%20the%20researchers%20told%20the%20Guardian%20that%20they%20believed%20the%20temperature%20was%20%26quot%3Btoo%20warm%20for%20water%20to%20be%20liquid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUniversit%C3%A9%20de%20Montr%C3%A9al%20Professor%20Bj%C3%B6rn%20Benneke%20said%20that%20surface%20temperatures%20on%20the%20exoplanet%20could%20be%20around%204%2C000%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20or%20around%207%2C200%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20this%20meant%20any%20water%20would%20be%20in%20a%20supercritical%20state%2C%20where%20%26quot%3Bit's%20almost%20like%20a%20thick%2C%20hot%20fluid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22image%20of%20the%20colorful%20nebula%20in%20space%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653fe053356802a56be791e0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221307%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Crab%20Nebula%20photographed%20by%20NASA's%20James%20Webb%20Space%20Telescope.%3Cp%3ENASA%2C%20ESA%2C%20CSA%2C%20STScI%2C%20Tea%20Temim%20(Princeton%20University)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20James%20Webb%20telescope%20has%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20advancing%20the%20search%20for%20habitable%20planets%20beyond%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20telescope%20intercepts%20infrared%20light%20and%20directs%20it%20to%20scientific%20instruments%20where%20it%20can%20be%20recorded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20its%20main%20uses%20is%20to%20study%20the%20atmospheres%20of%20exoplanets%20to%20see%20whether%20they%20could%20support%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20key%20that%20scientists%20look%20for%20in%20a%20potentially%20habitable%20planet%20is%20the%20presence%20of%20liquid%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20area%20around%20a%20star%20where%20water%20can%20exist%20in%20a%20liquid%20state%20is%20called%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fexoplanets.nasa.gov%2Ffaq%2F15%2Fwhat-is-the-habitable-zone-or-goldilocks-zone%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehabitable%20zone%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BGoldilocks'%20zone.%26quot%3B%20Planets%20in%20this%20zone%20are%20neither%20too%20hot%20nor%20too%20cold%20to%20support%20liquid%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.